# Types of method.

# Among all the method for beginner only focus on GET and POST method

# Get Metnod

Used to request (get) data from the server.
Example: text = request.GET['text']
{
    data is visible in URL
    used to searching, filtering, viewing pages
    should not change data
}

Example Use:
{
    Search bar
    Viewing a profile
    Reading data
}

# POST Method

Used to send data to the server to create/update something
Example: text = request.POST['text']
{
    Data is hidden from URL
    More secure than GET
    Used when submitting forms
}

Example use:
{
    Login form
    Registration
    Uload file
    submit comment
}

# PUT Method

Used to update existing data completely.

Example Use: 
{
    update full user profile. Mostly used in APIs (not basic Django forms).
}

# PATCH method

Used to update part of existing data.

Example:
{
    Only update user email, not full profile.
    Used in REST APIs.
}
